== Japanese content == {{出典の明記|date=2026-01}} {{神社 |名称= Murohime Shrine (Murohime Jinja) |画像= [[File:Aratano-murohime-shrine 2.jpg|250px]] |所在地= {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|qid=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Anan, Tokushima|Q485583|qid=Q485583|1=Anan, Tokushima}}{{ill|lt=Aratano-chō (Anan)|Q28686788|qid=Q28686788|lt=Aratano-chō|1=Aratanochō}} Iruta 136 |位置= {{WikidataCoord|display=inline,title}} |祭神= {{ill|lt=Konohanasakuya-hime|Q1781862|qid=Q1781862|lt=Murohime-no-Mikoto|1=Konohanasakuya-hime}} |社格= former unranked shrine |創建= unknown |本殿= |別名= |例祭= |神事= |地図= {{Location map|Japan Tokushima|label=室比賣神社|position=bottom|width=200|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=15|float=center|caption=}} {{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=10|marker=religious-shinto|frame-align=center|frame-width=200|frame-height=200}} }} '''Murohime Shrine''' (むろひめじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Aratano-chō (Anan)|Q28686788|qid=Q28686788|lt=Aratano-chō|1=Aratanochō}}, {{ill|lt=Anan, Tokushima|Q485583|qid=Q485583|1=Anan, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|qid=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}. It is also written as '''Murohime Jinja'''.
=== History === It was enshrined at {{ill|lt=Okayama Castle (Awa Province)|UNKNOWN|lt=Okayama Castle}} in the medieval period. On maps and shrine plaques it is written as '''Murohime Jinja''', but the Tokushima Prefecture Shrine Office lists it as Murohime Shrine.
The enshrined deity is "Murohi," the consort of {{ill|lt=Emperor Junnin|Q329713|qid=Q329713|1=Emperor Junnin}}. At the end of the {{ill|lt=Nara period|Q189178|qid=Q189178|1=Nara period}}, she is said to have longed for the emperor and set out for {{ill|lt=Awaji Island|Q504373|qid=Q504373|lt=Awaji|1=Awaji Island}} in a small boat, drifted ashore at this location, and was later enshrined here.
After being enshrined as Murohime Shrine, it was renamed Murohime Jinja in {{ill|lt=1874|Q7761|qid=Q7761|1=1874}} (Meiji 7).
=== Enshrined deity === * {{ill|lt=Konohanasakuya-hime|Q1781862|qid=Q1781862|lt=Murohime-no-Mikoto|1=Konohanasakuya-hime}}
=== Precincts === The shrine precincts are at the {{ill|lt=Okayama Castle (Awa Province)|UNKNOWN|lt=Okayama Castle ruins}}.
